25 ekatraika-samaye ca eka-icchāyām ca niścalatve ca,
26 yathā cakṣuṣī yad-ānandena calante
27 sahaivam nimagnānīva unmīlitāni ca bhavanti;

28 nava-prakāśānām ekatasya hṛdayāt
29 vāṇī pravṛttā, yā sūcīm tārāyām iva
30 mama tatraiva pravṛttau me darśayām āsa;

40 yadā samrāṭ saḥ yaḥ nityaṃ rājate
41 sainyāya saṃvidhānam cakāra, yaḥ saṃśaye āsīt,
42 kevalena anugraheṇa, na yathārthatvāt;

55 tasya madhye jātaḥ premamayī priyatamā
56 kṛṣṭīya viśvāsaḥ pavitraḥ yodhaḥ
57 svakīyeṣu dayāluḥ śatrūsu krūraḥ;

64 sā strī yaḥ tasya anujñām adāt,
65 svapne adṛśyat adbhutaṃ phalaṃ
66 yat tasmāt tasya ca santatirūpeṇa āgacchati sma;

85 Alpa-kāle mahān viśāradaḥ abhavat;
86 Tathā hi sa dṛākṣā-kṣetram parīkṣitum pravṛttaḥ;
87 Yat kṣetram kṣipraṃ śuklam bhavati, yadi dṛākṣā-rakṣakaḥ duṣṭaḥ syāt.

97 Tataḥ, siddhāntena saha icchāyā saha ca,
98 āpāstaulikakāryena pravartata,
99 yathā pravāhaḥ yaḥ unnatāyāḥ śirāyāḥ pracoditaḥ;

115 Tasya kulam, yat samyak pravṛttam āsīt
116 caraṇābhyām tasya padavīṣu, atipravṛttam asti,
117 yataḥ pūrvavartī aparaṃ pṛṣṭhataḥ kṣipati;

121 Satyam bruve, yaḥ patram patram anveṣayet
122 asmākam puṣṭakam, sa api prāpnoti patram
123 yatra pathitum śaknoti "Aham asmi yaḥ asmi";

133 Ugaḥ Saṃvittorātmakaḥ atraiva asti taiḥ saha,
134 tathā Pīteraḥ Maṃgīdātmakaḥ Pīteraśca Spānaḥ,
135 yaḥ adhastāt dvadaśasu pustakeṣu prakāśate;

142 Tathāvidhaṃ vīraṃ prabodhayitum
143 Mamaṃ pravṛttāvān ātmīyaḥ saujanyaṃ
144 Śrīmato Thomaḥ satī ca bhāṣā;
